    <h2 id="group_rides">Group Rides</h2>
    <p>
      We have regular no-drop group rides every week.
    </p>
    <h3><a name="pau_hana"></a>Pau Hana Wednesday - 35 miles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>When:</strong> Every Wednesday @ 4:30 p.m.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Where:</strong> Starting from Bikeadelic in Waikiki @ 4:30, or meet us at the
        fountain in Kapiolani Park as we roll past around 4:35.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>What:</strong> We ride from Waikiki out to Hanauma Bay, Sandy's Beach, or Makapu'u
        Point depending on the time of year and the weather. The ride is fast paced (18+ mph), but
        with a consistent route, regular regroup points, and a designated sweeper to ensure nobody
        gets left behind. On the way back we detour around Hawaii Kai, Nui Valley, and Hind Valley.
        We regroup at the Aloha Gas Station at Waialae and Kealaolu before heading back to Waikiki
        where we usually stop off somewhere for a beer or two, or three...
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Route:</strong>
        <a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/29339270">
          <img src="images/Pau Hana Route.png"
               alt="Pau Hana Route Map"
               class="group-ride-route-map" />
        </a>
        <ul>
          <li>East on Diamond Head Rd. / Kahala Ave.</li>
          <li>Left at the stop sign @ Kealaolu Rd.</li>
          <li>Regroup at the Aloha Gas Station on Waialae Ave.</li>
          <li>East on Kalaniana'ole Hwy.</li>
          <li>Regroup at the East end of Maunalua Beach Park.</li>
          <li>Continue East on Kalaniana'ole Hwy.</li>
          <li>Right onto Portlock</li>
          <li>Left onto Lawai St. to Nawiliwili St.</li>
          <li>Right back onto Kalaniana'ole Hwy.</li>
          <li>Regroup at the entrance to Hanauma Bay</li>
          <li>Weather and light permitting (announced at Hanauma):
            <ul>
              <li>Continue out to either Sandy's Beach, or Makapu'u point.</li>
              <li>Return via Kealahou St. and Hawaii Kai Dr.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Circuit around Kuapa Pond on Hawaii Kai Dr. & Kawaihae St.</li>
          <li>West Kalaniana'ole Hwy.</li>
          <li>Valleys:
            <ul>
              <li>Niu Valley</li>
              <li>Aina Haina</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>U-Turn at Waialae &amp; Kealaolu Rd.</li>
          <li>Regroup at the Aloha Gas Station.</li>
          <li>Back to Waikiki via Diamond Head.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
